      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Payment system",
      "fontSize": 28,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Payment system",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "QAZkh0qVAKHj30tnHOB0P",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 235,
      "y": 248.5,
      "width": 515.1796264648438,
      "height": 1325,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bVW",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 51642802,
      "version": 924,
      "versionNonce": 1409734066,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1782923348420,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Requirements clarification\n\nq. payment systm for e-commerce giants like amazon?\nyes\n\nq. scale\n10 million payments a day\n\nq. types of payments/\ncredit card, debit card, UPI ( india), paypal\n\nq. build payment rails or use 3rd party?\n3rd party like Stripe, adyen, paypal\n\nq. imp features?\npay in flow ( customer to amazon)\npay out flow ( amazon to sellers)\n\nq. global payments? currency\nyes, USD\n\nq. different providers in different countries?\nno for simplicity\n\nFunctional req:\npay in flow ( customer to amazon)\npay out flow ( amazon to sellers)\nReconciliation\nno double booking\n\nNFR:\nConsistent\nReliable and Fault toleranet\nscalable\nAvailability : 99.9\n\nBack of the envelope calc:\n\n10m transactions a day\n10 * 10^6 / 10^5 = 100 rps\n\nreads similar : 100 rps\n\nstorage :\n10 m transactions a day\neach transaction : 5 kb\n\n10 * 10^6 * 5 kb\n= 10^8 kb\n= 50 gb\n\n50 gb * 365 * 10\n= 183 tb",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Requirements clarification\n\nq. payment systm for e-commerce giants like amazon?\nyes\n\nq. scale\n10 million payments a day\n\nq. types of payments/\ncredit card, debit card, UPI ( india), paypal\n\nq. build payment rails or use 3rd party?\n3rd party like Stripe, adyen, paypal\n\nq. imp features?\npay in flow ( customer to amazon)\npay out flow ( amazon to sellers)\n\nq. global payments? currency\nyes, USD\n\nq. different providers in different countries?\nno for simplicity\n\nFunctional req:\npay in flow ( customer to amazon)\npay out flow ( amazon to sellers)\nReconciliation\nno double booking\n\nNFR:\nConsistent\nReliable and Fault toleranet\nscalable\nAvailability : 99.9\n\nBack of the envelope calc:\n\n10m transactions a day\n10 * 10^6 / 10^5 = 100 rps\n\nreads similar : 100 rps\n\nstorage :\n10 m transactions a day\neach transaction : 5 kb\n\n10 * 10^6 * 5 kb\n= 10^8 kb\n= 50 gb\n\n50 gb * 365 * 10\n= 183 tb",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
